com.enremmeta.rtb.api

Interface Tag

  • All Superinterfaces:
    KVKeysValues, Lot49Constants, Lot49Plugin, RtbConstants
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SharedSetUp.Tag_2002002_tagMarker_1001001_fake, TagImpl

    public interface Tag
extends Lot49Plugin
    Specifies configuration of a "tag".

    To keep the terminology straight, we define a "tag" to comprise two things:

    • Web tag - this is really what most users would think of. It is run in the browser - a piece of HTML/JS/VAST, etc. It is probably generated by an ad server.
    • Bid tag - a class implementing current interface. It is a piece of code run in the builder that is responsible for the following major functions (with default implementation provided by methods in TagImpl):
      Functionality Where implemented
      Holding the parameters of the web tag and creative (e.g., MIME types, dimensions, etc.) Various fields.
      Checking whether the specified impression request is a match canBid(OpenRtbRequest, Impression)
      Generating "web tag" to be sent to the browser. getTag(OpenRtbRequest, Impression, Bid, boolean)
      Generating Bid bid to be sent in the response to the bid request, containing the mentioned web tag as markup or as a reference getBid(OpenRtbRequest, Impression)

      Thus, in the simplest case, the author of this bid tag just needs to fill in the required fields and override getTagTemplate(OpenRtbRequest, Impression, Bid). However, for more advanced functionality, any method can be overridden.

    The naming convention for class names (and, therefore, filenames) to name them Tag_<TagID>_<TagName>_<AdId>_<AdName> where

      • getTag

        String getTag(OpenRtbRequest req,
              Impression imp,
              Bid bid,
              boolean nurl)
        Get the actual tag to send in the ad markup field of the bid (or in the response to nurl), based on the template.

        The provider of the template needs to understand the mechanism of macro substitution. The substitutions occur in the following order, each one going over the entire text of the template.

        1. No macro substitutions will be done to clickRedir or impRedir fields. If necessary, override the method appropriately.
        2. All occurrences of Macros.MACRO_LOT49_IMPRESSION will be replaced by the URL to the Lot49 impression tracker.
        3. TODO Proust
        4. Unless the exchange sends actual macros in a call to NUrl, the following click macro substitutions occur:
          1. All occurrences of Macros.MACRO_LOT49_CLICK_CHAIN_ENC are replaced as follows:
            • If there is an exchange click macro, then it is replaced with Macros.MACRO_LOT49_EXCHANGE_CLICK_ENC followed by Macros.MACRO_LOT49_CLICK_ENC_ENC.
            • If the exchange click macro does not exist, then this will be replaced by Macros.MACRO_LOT49_CLICK_ENC
            NOTE The replacement macros, in turn, can be replaced in later passes.
          2. All occurrences of Macros.MACRO_LOT49_CLICK_ENC_ENC will be replaced as Macros.MACRO_LOT49_CLICK (see below), except the replacement will be doubly URL-encoded.
          3. All occurrences of Macros.MACRO_LOT49_CLICK_ENC will be replaced as Macros.MACRO_LOT49_CLICK (see below), except the replacement will be URL-encoded.
          4. All occurrences of Macros.MACRO_LOT49_CLICK will be replaced by the URL to the Lot49 click tracker. If clickRedir is not null, this URL will include r query parameter whose value is URL-encoded clickRedir.
          5. All occurrences of Macros.MACRO_LOT49_EXCHANGE_CLICK_ENC will be replaced by the exchange-specific version thereof.
          6. All occurrences of Macros.MACRO_LOT49_EXCHANGE_CLICK will be replaced by the exchange-specific version thereof.
        5. Otherwise, the values for Macros.MACRO_LOT49_CLICK_ENC_ENC , Macros.MACRO_LOT49_CLICK_ENC and Macros.MACRO_LOT49_CLICK are generated, but not replaced. Instead, they are added to the NUrl, and will be substituted at NUrl invocation.
        See Also:
        ExchangeAdapter.isMacrosInNurl(), getTagTemplate(OpenRtbRequest, Impression, Bid), getImpressionUrl(OpenRtbRequest, Bid, boolean), getClickUrl(OpenRtbRequest, Bid), getBid(OpenRtbRequest, Impression)

      • getTagTemplate

        String getTagTemplate(OpenRtbRequest req,
                      Impression imp,
                      Bid bid)
        Tag template. This is pretty much the web tag that is intended to be sent to the browser, but what makes it a template is the fact that it may be parameterized by the following:
        1. Any of the fields of the class (that is, anything that has a no-argument getter, e.g. getMime().
        2. Any of the local variables which are up to the author of the class overriding this method to define and compute.
        3. Macros. The difference of these from the others is that the above substitutions are done during the invocation of this method, whereas the macros are substituted during the actual tag generation. It is at that point, for example, that click and impression tracking URLs are constructed.

          IMPORTANT It is up to the author of the implementing class to understand properly the web tag generation order and insert macros appropriately and encode URLs as needed

        See Also:
        getTag(OpenRtbRequest, Impression, Bid, boolean), getBid(OpenRtbRequest, Impression)
